data.hoverText: 可与单数或复数动词连用的可数名词

data.enText: a small group of people who are specially chosen and trained for a particular purpose
a member of this kind of group

tr: a nucleus of military personnel capable of expansion
a small unit serving as part of or as the nucleus of a larger political movement

value.def: A cadre is a small group of people who have been specially chosen, trained, and organized for a particular purpose.

example.tran: 国际经理人组成的精英队伍

value.def: In some political parties, especially the Communist Party, a cadre is a party worker or official.
value.tran: (尤指共产党的)党务工作者，干部
